organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Ah, I see. Sry, for the misunderstanding. Yes, a call of `Geometry.mergeVertices()` after the following line can't hurt.\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/cc06e7cbc2237b07f8a0cb59511037841c3877a2\/src\/core\/Geometry.js#L337-L338\r\n\r\n@ieskudero Would you like to do a PR with the change?","created_at":"2018-09-06T10:37:39.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14857#issuecomment-419047455","id":419047455,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14857","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxOTA0NzQ1NQ==","updated_at":"2018-09-06T10:38:38.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/419047455","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Ok, done, I think, this is the first time contributing to a project like this. Can you check if it is right, please?","created_at":"2018-09-06T12:19:12.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14857#issuecomment-419072711","id":419072711,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14857","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxOTA3MjcxMQ==","updated_at":"2018-09-06T12:19:12.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/419072711","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/20156458?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/ieskudero","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIwMTU2NDU4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"ieskudero","type":"User","id":20156458,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ieskudero\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I am not sure calling  `mergeVertices()` is a good idea. Think about the impact that will have on existing users. \r\n\r\nUsers can always call `mergeVertices()` themselves if that is what they want. Also, `mergeVertices()` has a hard-wired precision parameter.\r\n\r\n>Yes, a call of Geometry.mergeVertices() after the following line can't hurt.\r\n\r\nIf you insist on doing it anyway, I would call it _prior_ to computing face normals, not after.\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2018-09-06T18:47:02.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14857#issuecomment-419201548","id":419201548,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14857","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxOTIwMTU0OA==","updated_at":"2018-09-06T18:47:02.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/419201548","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":">  I would call it prior to computing face normals, not after.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure I understand the difference in this.\r\n\r\nIn any event, I think calling `.mergeVertices()` in this method should be implemented from the beginning.","created_at":"2018-09-06T19:18:22.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14857#issuecomment-419210711","id":419210711,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14857","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQxOTIxMDcxMQ==","updated_at":"2018-09-06T19:27:04.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/419210711","user":{"following_